                        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
                    </span>
                    <div class="info-tooltip-content absolute z-10 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 mt-2 w-72 p-3 bg-slate-800 text-white text-sm rounded-lg shadow-lg pointer-events-none">
                        This chart tracks the real value erosion of an initial €10,000 cash lump sum over 45 years, assuming 3% average inflation.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="text-center text-slate-500 mb-6 mt-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto">This visualization directly compares the Real Purchasing Power across three low-return scenarios (assuming 3% inflation).</p>
                
                <div class="chart-container chart-container-sm">
                    <canvas id="savingsInflationChart"></canvas>
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <!-- Section 5: Inflation Erosion (The original single chart, renamed for clarity) -->
            <section id="inflation-erosion-chart" class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-4 md:p-8 mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-2">Extreme Example: Money Under the Mattress (0% Return)</h2>
                <p class="text-center text-slate-500 mb-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">This chart isolates the single worst scenario: a 0% nominal return on €10,000. After 45 years, the purchasing power is decimated, losing nearly 75% of its original value.</p>
                <div class="chart-container chart-container-sm">
                    <canvas id="cashErosionChart"></canvas>
                </div>
